procstep.procdesc:
Study site locations were mapped using ArcGIS Pro 3.0.0. 5km and 50km buffers were generated using the Buffer tool. All work was done using ArcGIS Pro (version 3.0.0).

Landcover data downloaded for NLCD 2011 and C-CAP 2010, 2011, and 2012 were summarized for each sample location by: 
1) reprojecting and converting all C-CAP rasters from 3m to 30m cells to match the NLCD dataset; 
2) reclassifying C-CAP landcover categories to match NLCD landcover categories (C-CAP values 21, 22, 23 = NLCD 11; C-CAP 24, 25 = NLCD 12; C-CAP 5 = NLCD 21, C-CAP 4 = 22, C-CAP 3 = 23, C-CAP 2 = 24, C-CAP 19, 20 = 31, C-CAP 9 = 41, C-CAP 10 = 42, C-CAP 11 = 43, C-CAP 12 = 52, C-CAP 8 = 71, C-CAP 7 = 81, C-CAP 6 = 82, C-CAP 13, 14, 16, 17 = 90, C-CAP 15, 18 = 95);
3) generating area summaries of each landcover type within the 5km buffer for each site using the Zonal Statistics as Table tool.
